Gunman Kills Three Hostages at California Veterans Home
	 	 	 	 CONTENT 
SAN FRANCISCO—An armed standoff Friday at a veterans home in Yountville, Calif. ended with the discovery of four bodies by police, including the suspected gunman and three women thought to be his hostages, authorities said.

Police tactical teams made the discovery at about 6 p.m. Friday, hours after the gunman stormed into a building on the campus of the Veterans Home of California, a state-operated facility in the heart of Napa Valley wine country and began taking hostages at about 10:30 a.m. A Napa County sheriff’s deputy...
